maintitle: Linux Setup and Useful Apps for Ubuntu/Debian Distros

---

title: Update System
note: Run this anytime you want to fully update your system from the terminal.
step: go to terminal and do this
bash:
sudo apt update -y && sudo apt upgrade -y && sudo apt autoremove

---

title: Update Drivers <mark>Linux Mint</mark>
bash:
sudo apt update && sudo apt full-upgrade -y
# Driver Manager (pick NVIDIA/prop if needed)
bash:
sudo mintdrivers
note: If you end up installing any drivers from that, it could be wise to reboot
bash:
sudo reboot

---

title: Install the Ubuntu Driver Collection
bash:
sudo apt install -y ubuntu-drivers-common
sudo ubuntu-drivers install
sudo reboot

---

title: Install Nvidia Drive
note: ⚠️ Only do this if you have an NVidia GPU!
bash:
sudo apt install -y nvidia-driver

---

title: Install Multimedia Support
bash:
sudo apt install -y mint-meta-codecs
sudo apt install -y libavcodec-extra vlc

---

title: Improve Battery & Power Management (Approach 1)
note: ⚠️ Only do this if you're setting up a laptop
bash:
sudo apt install -y tlp tlp-rdw
sudo systemctl enable --now tlp

---

title: Improve Battery & Power Management (Approach 2 - <mark>May manage both battery life and cpu power monitoring, unlike tlp, which foces on battery</mark>)
note: ⚠️ Only do this if you're setting up a laptop
item: Uninstall tlp, if it's installed
bash:
sudo apt autoremove tlp
item: Install auto-cpufreq
bash:
git clone https://github.com/AdnanHodzic/auto-cpufreq.git
cd auto-cpufreq && sudo ./auto-cpufreq-installer

